aiken/merkle_patricia_forestry/Neighbor.title: Neighbor
aiken/merkle_patricia_forestry/Neighbor.description: A neighbor node used in a proof. See [Proof](#Proof) for details.

aiken/merkle_patricia_forestry/ProofStep.title: ProofStep
aiken/merkle_patricia_forestry/ProofStep.description:
We distinguish three kind of proof steps: Branch, Fork and Leaf. Each step
 contains a `skip` value which corresponds to the length of the common prefix
 at that particular level.

 The details of each level is documented [in the wiki :: Proof Format](https://github.com/aiken-lang/merkle-patricia-forestry/wiki/Proof-format).

aiken/transaction/OutputReference.title: OutputReference
aiken/transaction/OutputReference.description:
An `OutputReference` is a unique reference to an output on-chain. The `output_index`
 corresponds to the position in the output list of the transaction (identified by its id)
 that produced that output

aiken/transaction/TransactionId.title: TransactionId
aiken/transaction/TransactionId.description:
A unique transaction identifier, as the hash of a transaction body. Note that the transaction id
 isn't a direct hash of the `Transaction` as visible on-chain. Rather, they correspond to hash
 digests of transaction body as they are serialized on the network.

anyOf.title: HardFork
anyOf.description: This action is only run once and it sets up the ability to convert v1 tuna tokens to v2 tuna tokens

simplerfork/LockState.title: LockState
simplerfork/LockState.description:
Simplified fork with only 2 actions. HardFork current tuna v1 version to v2 version
 and Lock action to lock v1 tokens and mint v2 tokens. This is simpler version that does not have miners'
 input in the hardfork action. This is mainly because there are no current miners anyway.
 Ensures that maximum lockable tuna is equal to emitted tuna at block height
